WEBVTT

00:00:05.023 --> 00:00:06.183
Tom, why did you invite monks?

00:00:06.223 --> 00:00:08.383
Didn’t Win say this house is haunted?

00:00:08.423 --> 00:00:10.303
Then please go all out, Father.

00:00:14.103 --> 00:00:15.183
You again?

00:00:15.223 --> 00:00:16.983
You followed me all the way to my house?

00:00:17.023 --> 00:00:18.063
I’m going to report you…

00:00:18.103 --> 00:00:21.063
- Hey, hey!
- Get out of my house!

00:00:21.103 --> 00:00:23.623
No... please don’t kick me out.

00:00:23.903 --> 00:00:25.903
I really am the owner of this house.

00:00:25.903 --> 00:00:28.183
- I really live here, I…
- Fine, you can stay.

00:00:28.223 --> 00:00:30.503
But we need to agree on some conditions first.

00:00:30.903 --> 00:00:32.103
Wanneung.

00:00:32.103 --> 00:00:34.943
I can’t sleep when the power’s out.
Let me sleep with you.

00:01:52.703 --> 00:01:54.903
The electricity should
be back this morning, right?

00:01:56.223 --> 00:01:57.623
Last night…

00:01:58.103 --> 00:01:59.903
The AC was freezing, huh?

00:02:08.823 --> 00:02:10.423
I’m gonna take a shower.

00:02:23.383 --> 00:02:25.103
My shoes…

00:02:26.023 --> 00:02:27.103
Oh.

00:02:49.983 --> 00:02:52.303
Why are my cheeks so red?

00:04:31.783 --> 00:04:35.423
Excuse me, I’m crossing the line
to grab something from the fridge.

00:05:04.423 --> 00:05:06.783
Oh no, I overcooked the fried egg.

00:05:07.223 --> 00:05:09.023
Guess I’ll have to toss it and make a new one.

00:05:09.503 --> 00:05:12.303
Hey, hey, no need to make a new one.

00:05:12.583 --> 00:05:14.183
That’d just be a waste.

00:05:14.183 --> 00:05:16.183
Do you know what food waste is?

00:05:16.223 --> 00:05:18.103
I’ll help you eat it.

00:05:20.223 --> 00:05:21.383
It’s nothing, really.

00:05:21.423 --> 00:05:23.623
I just hate wasting food.

00:05:26.423 --> 00:05:27.623
Thank you.

00:05:30.423 --> 00:05:32.703
Mmm, smells so good.

00:05:33.983 --> 00:05:35.023
Wait…

00:05:37.023 --> 00:05:40.103
Didn’t you say you wouldn’t throw it away?

00:05:41.503 --> 00:05:43.223
You’ve got more sides?

00:05:44.503 --> 00:05:46.903
Can I get some bacon too?

00:05:49.023 --> 00:05:50.183
Thank you.

00:05:50.223 --> 00:05:54.223
I promise I’ll finish every last bite.

00:06:06.103 --> 00:06:09.303
Hey... how did you know I like

00:06:09.303 --> 00:06:11.703
my fried eggs well done like this?

00:06:12.023 --> 00:06:14.623
I like them a little crispy like this.

00:06:15.023 --> 00:06:17.303
Your bacon is really good.

00:06:26.383 --> 00:06:27.903
Hello, Mom.

00:06:28.503 --> 00:06:30.383
Win’s been pretty busy lately,

00:06:30.423 --> 00:06:32.223
so I haven’t stopped by.

00:06:32.303 --> 00:06:33.623
Today?

00:06:34.703 --> 00:06:37.223
Okay, I’ll drop by the house.

00:06:38.103 --> 00:06:39.423
Alright. Bye.

00:06:59.823 --> 00:07:00.823
You…

00:07:00.823 --> 00:07:02.423
What are you doing in my car?

00:07:02.903 --> 00:07:05.783
Well... you’re heading to Bang Bua Thong, right?

00:07:05.823 --> 00:07:07.903
I’ve got work around there anyway.

00:07:07.903 --> 00:07:09.823
Can I get a ride with you?

00:07:10.103 --> 00:07:11.783
Please... Win?

00:07:11.823 --> 00:07:14.503
Please, pretty please...

00:07:16.503 --> 00:07:19.263
I really need to save money right now.

00:07:19.303 --> 00:07:23.103
I have to pay the electricity bill this month
because I lost that bet to you.

00:07:24.623 --> 00:07:25.823
Wait a second…

00:07:27.023 --> 00:07:29.503
How did you know I’m going to Bang Bua Thong?

00:07:29.983 --> 00:07:32.223
Well... you’re going to see your mom, right?

00:07:32.423 --> 00:07:34.103
I asked ChatGPT.

00:07:34.103 --> 00:07:35.903
Your mom’s house is around there.

00:07:36.903 --> 00:07:38.503
Come on, you’ll be late.

00:07:38.543 --> 00:07:40.023
Didn’t you make plans with your mom?

00:07:40.103 --> 00:07:41.263
Let’s go, hurry.

00:07:41.303 --> 00:07:43.703
What is this? You’re unbelievable.

00:07:44.023 --> 00:07:45.823
So annoying. Get out.

00:07:48.223 --> 00:07:50.423
Didn’t you say you’d let me come?

00:07:50.903 --> 00:07:52.103
Get out.

00:07:53.023 --> 00:07:56.583
Win, please let me come with you.

00:07:56.623 --> 00:07:58.503
Get out and close the gate.

00:08:01.303 --> 00:08:02.303
Okay.

00:08:03.023 --> 00:08:05.423
Let’s call it payment for the ride.

00:08:57.223 --> 00:08:58.223
Win.

00:09:05.503 --> 00:09:06.503
Wait.

00:09:07.503 --> 00:09:09.103
Hello, May.

00:09:09.223 --> 00:09:11.103
I need to talk to you.

00:09:11.783 --> 00:09:13.903
With... me?

00:09:15.623 --> 00:09:17.223
Who dropped you off just now?

00:09:21.983 --> 00:09:24.703
- A friend.
- Don’t lie. That was Win, wasn’t it?

00:09:27.503 --> 00:09:28.703
Hold on.

00:09:29.103 --> 00:09:30.783
All this time,

00:09:30.823 --> 00:09:33.223
you’ve never cared about someone like me.

00:09:33.303 --> 00:09:35.983
But today, you suddenly want to talk.

00:09:36.023 --> 00:09:38.063
Is it because you think the one who dropped me off

00:09:38.103 --> 00:09:39.783
So was Win Pawee?

00:09:39.783 --> 00:09:41.423
Was it?

00:09:41.423 --> 00:09:43.983
Well... Was it...??

00:09:44.023 --> 00:09:45.783
Was it...?

00:09:45.783 --> 00:09:47.503
You’re just an extra, right?

00:09:47.623 --> 00:09:49.983
- Yes.
- You can go change now.

00:09:50.023 --> 00:09:51.023
Okay.

00:09:52.823 --> 00:09:54.463
May, please wait a moment.

00:09:54.503 --> 00:09:57.103
They’re almost done setting the scene and lights.

00:09:57.143 --> 00:09:58.223
Alright.

00:09:59.423 --> 00:10:00.623
Excuse me.

00:10:00.703 --> 00:10:04.183
Wrap is at 4 PM today, right?
I have something after this.

00:10:04.223 --> 00:10:05.303
Yes.

00:10:05.623 --> 00:10:06.703
Thank you.

00:10:29.223 --> 00:10:31.783
Mom made a lot of your favorite dishes.

00:10:31.823 --> 00:10:34.903
Put it in the fridge,
so you can heat it up when you’re hungry.

00:10:35.303 --> 00:10:37.463
You’ve gotten so skinny lately.

00:10:37.503 --> 00:10:39.303
Haven’t you been eating, sweetie?

00:11:34.503 --> 00:11:36.383
So… I ran out of stuff,

00:11:36.423 --> 00:11:38.863
so I borrowed some of yours to eat.

00:11:38.903 --> 00:11:41.383
But I’ll go buy some to replace it.

00:11:41.423 --> 00:11:42.663
I’m sorry.

00:11:42.703 --> 00:11:45.223
I’ll really go buy it back, I promise.

00:12:07.103 --> 00:12:10.383
About getting Win to star in the film,

00:12:10.423 --> 00:12:11.823
I haven’t decided yet.

00:12:11.823 --> 00:12:15.063
Waanwaan introduced another kid to me,

00:12:15.103 --> 00:12:16.263
her name’s Gam.

00:12:16.303 --> 00:12:18.303
I think she’s interesting.

00:12:18.303 --> 00:12:20.383
She’s still fresh,

00:12:20.383 --> 00:12:21.703
hasn’t been overexposed yet.

00:12:23.023 --> 00:12:24.303
But seriously,

00:12:24.303 --> 00:12:27.383
if you get Win and May as a pair
and I direct,

00:12:27.423 --> 00:12:30.503
the credit looks way better
than casting a no-name kid.

00:12:30.703 --> 00:12:33.383
And besides, didn’t you say

00:12:33.423 --> 00:12:34.983
the role is tough?

00:12:35.023 --> 00:12:37.783
If you cast someone inexperienced,

00:12:37.823 --> 00:12:39.503
you’ll just tire yourself out.

00:12:41.023 --> 00:12:42.223
Well…

00:12:42.503 --> 00:12:45.183
I did contact Win,
but she hasn’t replied yet.

00:12:45.223 --> 00:12:47.503
Then I’ll reach out to her.

00:13:03.903 --> 00:13:06.343
(May)

00:13:13.503 --> 00:13:14.903
Hello, May.

00:13:14.983 --> 00:13:16.383
Hi, Win.

00:13:16.423 --> 00:13:18.383
Director Tong wants to talk to you.

00:13:18.423 --> 00:13:20.023
He’s on the line right now.

00:13:20.503 --> 00:13:21.503
Uh…

00:13:26.103 --> 00:13:27.703
Hello, P’Tong.

00:13:28.583 --> 00:13:30.463
Meedee, about the vitamins I asked you to buy,

00:13:30.503 --> 00:13:31.863
you can keep them for now.

00:13:31.903 --> 00:13:33.903
I’ll drop by the hospital to get them later.

00:13:33.903 --> 00:13:35.103
Talk later.

00:13:51.103 --> 00:13:54.503
Wow, that’s a lot of stuff,
Sup'tar Win Pawee.

00:13:55.023 --> 00:13:57.343
You bought so much.

00:13:57.423 --> 00:13:59.983
There’s no way you can finish all that alone.

00:13:59.983 --> 00:14:01.863
It’ll expire first.

00:14:01.903 --> 00:14:04.503
I’ll help you eat it then.

00:14:04.703 --> 00:14:08.023
Just so it doesn’t expire.
Not that I want to eat it or anything.

00:14:16.223 --> 00:14:18.383
You… why did you buy so much stuff?

00:14:18.423 --> 00:14:20.783
It’s going to expire, you know.

00:14:20.823 --> 00:14:22.983
I… I didn’t mean to.

00:14:22.983 --> 00:14:25.023
I mean, you bought…

00:14:32.223 --> 00:14:33.623
What’s wrong with her?

00:14:53.903 --> 00:14:55.023
What’s wrong?

00:15:03.103 --> 00:15:04.223
Who’s here?

00:15:06.023 --> 00:15:07.783
Is it your fan?

00:15:07.823 --> 00:15:09.903
Or maybe a sasaeng?

00:15:11.503 --> 00:15:14.623
Or did some news about you leak,
so reporters followed you here?

00:15:16.023 --> 00:15:17.223
Go check it out.

00:15:17.503 --> 00:15:19.303
I suddenly need to pee.

00:15:20.503 --> 00:15:22.703
- Go check for me.
- Me?

00:15:22.903 --> 00:15:25.263
Is that a good idea?
Isn’t this your house?

00:15:25.303 --> 00:15:27.063
- I’ll pay this month’s electricity bill.
- For real?

00:15:27.103 --> 00:15:30.063
- For real.
- And… the stuff in the fridge?

00:15:30.103 --> 00:15:31.263
Can I eat it?

00:15:31.303 --> 00:15:33.583
You sneak some all the time anyway.

00:15:33.583 --> 00:15:34.863
Why even ask?

00:15:34.903 --> 00:15:36.983
I only eat the ones near expiry.

00:15:37.023 --> 00:15:38.663
I told you, I hate food waste.

00:15:38.703 --> 00:15:41.703
You’re the one who keeps buying too much.

00:15:41.903 --> 00:15:43.383
Go check already. Hurry.

00:15:43.423 --> 00:15:47.223
- Go.
- Should I really go…?

00:15:47.503 --> 00:15:48.503
Wanneung.

00:15:49.503 --> 00:15:51.263
If you’re not going to be useful,

00:15:51.303 --> 00:15:53.303
then pack your things and leave my house.

00:15:53.383 --> 00:15:55.503
I can call the village security.

00:15:56.903 --> 00:16:00.983
We’re… housemates living together.

00:16:01.023 --> 00:16:04.023
We should help each other.
Fine, I’ll go check.

00:16:15.423 --> 00:16:17.263
Meedee? What are you doing here?

00:16:17.303 --> 00:16:20.263
Why did you take so long?
What were you doing?

00:16:20.303 --> 00:16:23.063
Meedee, I was in the bathroom just now.

00:16:23.063 --> 00:16:24.303
I just finished.

00:16:26.423 --> 00:16:27.623
The vitamins.

00:16:27.903 --> 00:16:29.783
I told you not to come.

00:16:29.823 --> 00:16:31.423
I was going to pick them up at the hospital.

00:16:31.423 --> 00:16:32.623
Seriously, you…

00:16:32.703 --> 00:16:34.663
I called you earlier,

00:16:34.703 --> 00:16:36.623
but you hung up first.

00:16:37.503 --> 00:16:39.823
Take the vitamins.

00:16:39.903 --> 00:16:41.223
So you won’t get sick.

00:16:41.503 --> 00:16:43.263
Thanks. Thank you.

00:16:43.303 --> 00:16:44.303
Wait…

00:16:44.623 --> 00:16:46.103
Are you kicking me out already?

00:16:46.303 --> 00:16:48.223
Aren’t you going to invite me in?

00:16:49.623 --> 00:16:51.903
If you treat me like this, I’ll feel hurt.

00:16:52.023 --> 00:16:54.263
Since when do friends feel hurt like that?

00:16:54.303 --> 00:16:56.303
Come on, Meedee. You should go.

00:16:57.703 --> 00:17:00.023
I’m really hungry.

00:17:00.423 --> 00:17:01.983
Let me eat with you.

00:17:01.983 --> 00:17:04.303
I haven’t eaten anything since my shift ended.

00:17:04.823 --> 00:17:05.823
Or…

00:17:06.303 --> 00:17:08.503
are you going to fry me an egg here?

00:17:12.903 --> 00:17:15.423
My treat. There’s a made-to-order
place at the end of the alley.

00:17:15.463 --> 00:17:16.783
Just go, Meedee.

00:17:16.823 --> 00:17:17.983
Come with me.

00:17:18.023 --> 00:17:19.783
Here she goes again.

00:17:19.823 --> 00:17:21.463
I can’t deal with this, Meedee.

00:17:21.503 --> 00:17:22.983
Take the vitamins too.

00:17:23.023 --> 00:17:24.183
So you won’t get diarrhea.

00:17:24.223 --> 00:17:26.583
- Okay, okay.
- Give it back.

00:17:26.583 --> 00:17:29.103
Bye-bye, Meedee. I’m done.

00:17:29.103 --> 00:17:30.183
Bye-bye.

00:17:30.223 --> 00:17:31.823
Bye, Meedee.

00:17:49.343 --> 00:17:50.743
Wanneung

00:17:52.623 --> 00:17:54.303
What were you doing over there?

00:17:54.383 --> 00:17:55.663
Has she left?

00:17:56.303 --> 00:17:57.623
Yeah, she’s gone.

00:18:06.583 --> 00:18:08.023
So who was it?

00:18:08.823 --> 00:18:11.423
My friend. She dropped something off.

00:18:12.223 --> 00:18:13.663
Your friend?

00:18:13.703 --> 00:18:16.063
You knew your friend was coming.

00:18:16.103 --> 00:18:17.503
Why didn’t you tell me?

00:18:18.223 --> 00:18:19.703
That’s cheating.

00:18:20.103 --> 00:18:22.303
Fine, I’m not paying the electricity bill this month.

00:18:32.223 --> 00:18:34.463
I’ve only got a little over a thousand baht left.

00:18:34.503 --> 00:18:36.183
That has to last all month.

00:18:36.223 --> 00:18:38.583
If you still force me to pay the bill,

00:18:38.623 --> 00:18:40.263
I won’t be able to come up with it.

00:18:40.303 --> 00:18:42.103
Your house will get cut off.

00:18:44.103 --> 00:18:45.823
Or…

00:18:45.903 --> 00:18:48.663
do you want to stay in the dark,

00:18:48.703 --> 00:18:51.463
all creepy at night,

00:18:51.503 --> 00:18:52.983
and let ghosts haunt you?

00:18:53.023 --> 00:18:54.103
Wanneung.

00:19:13.983 --> 00:19:14.983
What are you doing?

00:19:17.063 --> 00:19:18.143
I’m not doing anything.

00:19:18.143 --> 00:19:19.343
Can you get up now?

00:19:20.223 --> 00:19:21.583
Hey, who are you?

00:19:21.583 --> 00:19:23.583
How did you get into my friend’s house?

00:20:27.709 --> 00:20:29.469
Did you turn Director Tong down

00:20:29.509 --> 00:20:30.589
because of May?

00:20:30.589 --> 00:20:32.669
Think it through first. Don’t rush it.

00:20:32.709 --> 00:20:35.789
He said you still have time to decide.

00:20:36.709 --> 00:20:37.709
What are you doing?

00:20:47.189 --> 00:20:48.349
I’m not doing anything.

00:20:48.389 --> 00:20:52.709
I’m not reading the message
your girlfriend sent you… either.

00:20:58.989 --> 00:21:00.309
Win…

00:21:00.389 --> 00:21:02.309
are you mad at me?

00:21:02.389 --> 00:21:04.509
I’m sorry.

00:21:06.509 --> 00:21:07.709
Can you get up now?

00:21:07.789 --> 00:21:09.269
Get up from what?

00:21:34.389 --> 00:21:35.469
Did you…

00:21:35.509 --> 00:21:37.309
have a fight with your girlfriend?

00:21:38.989 --> 00:21:41.669
This morning, she asked about you too.

00:21:41.709 --> 00:21:44.989
She was surprised you drove me to the set.

00:21:45.789 --> 00:21:47.869
But I didn’t say anything.

00:21:47.869 --> 00:21:51.789
I don’t meddle in other people’s
personal business. You know that.

00:21:53.709 --> 00:21:55.389
May isn’t my girlfriend.

00:21:55.709 --> 00:21:57.109
We’re just friends.

00:21:57.269 --> 00:21:58.509
But earlier…

00:22:04.389 --> 00:22:06.389
We can’t love each other.

00:22:07.789 --> 00:22:09.589
We’re too different.

00:22:10.069 --> 00:22:12.589
I’m just someone worthless.

00:22:12.789 --> 00:22:15.389
I could never reach up
to love someone like you.

00:22:16.109 --> 00:22:17.909
Don’t look down on yourself.

00:22:18.589 --> 00:22:21.189
We’re just ordinary people.

00:22:21.589 --> 00:22:23.389
Why can’t we love each other?

00:22:31.869 --> 00:22:33.109
No.

00:22:33.909 --> 00:22:35.269
This isn’t right.

00:22:36.109 --> 00:22:38.069
If anyone finds out,

00:22:38.109 --> 00:22:39.549
it won’t look good.

00:22:39.589 --> 00:22:40.669
Love…

00:22:40.709 --> 00:22:42.189
there’s no right or wrong.

00:22:42.909 --> 00:22:45.309
There’s only love or not love.

00:22:48.589 --> 00:22:50.109
For me…

00:22:51.389 --> 00:22:52.989
you’re the one I love.

00:22:54.589 --> 00:22:56.109
I love you.

00:23:10.389 --> 00:23:11.389
What’s wrong?

00:23:29.189 --> 00:23:31.189
Why are your face and ears all red?

00:23:32.509 --> 00:23:34.509
You’re blushing over just a movie?

00:23:47.989 --> 00:23:49.669
I’m sleepy.

00:23:49.709 --> 00:23:51.909
I’m going to bed.

00:23:53.509 --> 00:23:54.909
Sleepy.

00:24:15.989 --> 00:24:17.789
Hey, who are you?

00:24:18.389 --> 00:24:20.389
How did you get into my friend’s house?

00:24:21.309 --> 00:24:22.909
Well…

00:24:22.989 --> 00:24:25.709
- I…
- Tom.

00:24:26.389 --> 00:24:29.349
- You’re back?
- Yeah, just got home.

00:24:29.389 --> 00:24:30.589
So I dropped by.

00:24:30.989 --> 00:24:32.549
I brought the script too.

00:24:32.589 --> 00:24:33.989
In case you want to read it.

00:24:35.709 --> 00:24:37.269
I already said I’m not doing it.

00:24:37.309 --> 00:24:39.669
Come on… just read it first.

00:24:39.709 --> 00:24:41.309
It’s really good.

00:24:54.109 --> 00:24:55.189
By the way…

00:24:55.589 --> 00:24:57.189
who is this woman?

00:24:58.989 --> 00:25:00.349
The former owner.

00:25:00.389 --> 00:25:03.309
She’s staying temporarily
while looking for a new place.

00:25:04.109 --> 00:25:05.909
And you’re letting her stay?

00:25:05.989 --> 00:25:07.589
What if she’s a scammer?

00:25:07.789 --> 00:25:09.589
Why do you trust people so easily?

00:25:10.269 --> 00:25:11.589
Hey…

00:25:11.709 --> 00:25:13.389
watch your words.

00:25:13.389 --> 00:25:14.949
Do I look like a thief?

00:25:14.989 --> 00:25:17.069
I’m dressed this cute.

00:25:17.069 --> 00:25:19.669
Look at my blue plaid outfit.

00:25:21.909 --> 00:25:23.469
You’re tiny as a puppy.

00:25:23.509 --> 00:25:25.309
One throw and you’d pass out.

00:25:25.389 --> 00:25:27.269
So clumsy too.

00:25:27.309 --> 00:25:29.149
You wouldn’t make it as a thief.

00:25:29.189 --> 00:25:31.709
You can barely take care of yourself.

00:25:31.989 --> 00:25:33.509
Win…

00:25:34.789 --> 00:25:36.789
don’t underestimate me.

00:25:38.509 --> 00:25:40.989
Rule number one: no crossing the line.

00:26:00.589 --> 00:26:02.829
- Cut. Scene twenty-one.
- Yes.

00:26:02.869 --> 00:26:04.789
Okay… hold for a second.

00:26:04.909 --> 00:26:06.109
Memorize your lines.

00:26:18.109 --> 00:26:19.109
Hey, you.

00:26:21.789 --> 00:26:23.069
My name’s P’Man.

00:26:23.109 --> 00:26:24.309
I’m a modeling agent.

00:26:27.189 --> 00:26:28.989
Have you signed with anyone yet?

00:26:29.509 --> 00:26:30.989
Interested in signing with me?

00:26:31.989 --> 00:26:33.389
Really?

00:26:33.589 --> 00:26:35.189
You’re interested in me?

00:26:35.909 --> 00:26:37.909
You’re not lying, right?

00:26:39.189 --> 00:26:41.349
Of course not. Why would I lie?

00:26:41.389 --> 00:26:43.509
Everyone on this set knows me.

00:26:44.189 --> 00:26:46.909
Okay. I believe you.

00:26:47.069 --> 00:26:50.949
So if I’m interested, what do I have to do?

00:26:50.989 --> 00:26:52.949
Let’s exchange LINE first.

00:26:52.989 --> 00:26:55.389
- Then you…
- Wanneung.

00:26:55.389 --> 00:26:56.829
Wanneung.

00:26:57.269 --> 00:26:58.389
Tomorrow,

00:26:59.069 --> 00:27:00.669
come to my company’s address.

00:27:00.669 --> 00:27:02.709
We’ll do a screen test.

00:27:03.389 --> 00:27:05.229
Someone like you…

00:27:06.869 --> 00:27:08.229
you’ll definitely get the job.

00:27:08.469 --> 00:27:10.149
Yes, P’Man.

00:27:12.909 --> 00:27:14.109
Here’s my LINE.

00:27:15.669 --> 00:27:16.989
Okay.

00:27:39.349 --> 00:27:40.709
Tom knows

00:27:40.989 --> 00:27:42.509
you’re still hurting.

00:27:42.789 --> 00:27:44.509
From what May did to you.

00:27:45.149 --> 00:27:47.149
And you probably haven’t forgotten.

00:27:49.669 --> 00:27:51.029
If you know that,

00:27:51.069 --> 00:27:54.829
- why are you still pushing me to act with her?
- Win.

00:27:55.069 --> 00:27:58.029
Separate work from personal stuff.

00:27:58.389 --> 00:28:00.309
This is a great opportunity.

00:28:00.669 --> 00:28:03.109
For you to rebuild your name.

00:28:03.189 --> 00:28:04.709
I don’t want that.

00:28:05.269 --> 00:28:07.429
I just want my own life.

00:28:08.269 --> 00:28:10.229
Fame, to me…

00:28:10.389 --> 00:28:12.109
it doesn’t matter anymore.

00:28:12.869 --> 00:28:15.309
But someone like May won’t give up easily.

00:28:15.789 --> 00:28:17.029
You know that.

00:28:17.189 --> 00:28:18.349
If May

00:28:18.789 --> 00:28:20.629
wants something,

00:28:25.589 --> 00:28:28.509
Then you’ll have to be firm about this.

00:28:37.989 --> 00:28:39.189
Win…

00:28:41.989 --> 00:28:44.269
Why are you smiling like that?
Did you win the lottery?

00:28:44.309 --> 00:28:46.029
Even better than that.

00:28:46.069 --> 00:28:48.149
I’m about to become an actress.

00:28:48.189 --> 00:28:50.469
Someone wants to sign me as their artist.

00:28:50.469 --> 00:28:53.029
I’m about to be famous.
I’m just excited.

00:28:53.589 --> 00:28:56.189
You really want to be an actress, huh?

00:28:56.309 --> 00:28:57.469
Of course, Win.

00:28:57.469 --> 00:28:59.909
I’ve only ever had one dream.

00:28:59.909 --> 00:29:01.629
To become a superstar.

00:29:01.669 --> 00:29:04.469
I want fame, I want people to love me.

00:29:04.469 --> 00:29:06.269
I want people to admire me.

00:29:06.269 --> 00:29:09.029
And now my dream is finally coming true.

00:29:09.029 --> 00:29:11.029
I’m really excited, Win.

00:29:17.909 --> 00:29:19.029
How about this…

00:29:19.589 --> 00:29:21.069
go get dressed up,

00:29:21.109 --> 00:29:22.709
I’ll take you out to celebrate.

00:29:24.709 --> 00:29:26.149
Go get dressed.

00:29:26.189 --> 00:29:28.069
I’ll take you to dinner.
You coming or not?

00:29:28.109 --> 00:29:29.429
Dinner?

00:29:29.989 --> 00:29:31.189
Let’s go.

00:29:39.589 --> 00:29:42.669
If you’re planning something,
just say it.

00:29:44.069 --> 00:29:45.629
You’re smarter than I thought.

00:30:04.949 --> 00:30:06.349
Where’s the love?

00:30:06.349 --> 00:30:09.389
I’ve grown up all this time
and never once felt it.

00:30:09.389 --> 00:30:10.709
Do you even really want to be an actress?

00:30:10.709 --> 00:30:12.109
What’s wrong with how I did it?

00:30:12.109 --> 00:30:13.509
What part wasn’t good?

00:30:13.509 --> 00:30:14.949
Every part of it was bad.

00:30:42.960 --> 00:30:46.000
Is there something special
about you asking me out today?

00:30:49.080 --> 00:30:50.920
I want to talk to you.

00:30:51.280 --> 00:30:52.480
About what?

00:30:53.760 --> 00:30:54.920
About us.

00:30:55.160 --> 00:30:56.800
About us?

00:30:58.080 --> 00:30:59.880
What do you mean?

00:31:01.080 --> 00:31:02.920
You should stop contacting me.

00:31:04.280 --> 00:31:05.680
There’s no point.

00:31:06.080 --> 00:31:08.520
When I’m hurt, I remember.
You know that.

00:31:08.680 --> 00:31:09.800
Win…

00:31:10.160 --> 00:31:11.360
I understand.

00:31:11.360 --> 00:31:13.440
I know I was wrong, but…

00:31:13.760 --> 00:31:16.320
- I just want another chance.
- And about the movie…

00:31:21.160 --> 00:31:22.280
The movie.

00:31:23.040 --> 00:31:25.920
You’ve read the script, right?
Are you taking it?

00:31:26.000 --> 00:31:27.240
I haven’t read it.

00:31:27.280 --> 00:31:29.200
And I don’t plan to.

00:31:29.280 --> 00:31:30.320
Win…

00:31:30.760 --> 00:31:32.600
This is serious.

00:31:32.960 --> 00:31:36.120
I talked to the director
to get you this role.

00:31:36.280 --> 00:31:39.000
And everyone wants this part.

00:31:39.360 --> 00:31:42.320
The press launch is coming up soon.

00:31:42.360 --> 00:31:44.040
What are you waiting for?

00:31:44.360 --> 00:31:46.560
Why do you want me to play this role so badly?

00:31:46.600 --> 00:31:49.440
Because it’ll make you famous again.

00:31:49.480 --> 00:31:51.200
And more importantly…

00:31:51.280 --> 00:31:53.640
I want to do this movie with you.

00:31:53.640 --> 00:31:55.000
I don’t want to.

00:31:55.080 --> 00:31:56.680
I don’t want to be famous again.

00:31:56.760 --> 00:31:58.120
And most importantly…

00:31:59.080 --> 00:32:00.840
I don’t want to act with you.

00:32:01.360 --> 00:32:04.680
Win… why can’t we even talk properly?

00:32:07.360 --> 00:32:08.920
Have you been waiting long?

00:32:11.280 --> 00:32:12.520
You…

00:32:14.840 --> 00:32:17.120
H-Hi, Khun May.

00:32:19.960 --> 00:32:21.400
Let’s go.

00:32:21.880 --> 00:32:25.040
Oh? I thought we were celebrating here.

00:32:25.080 --> 00:32:26.240
Better not.

00:32:26.280 --> 00:32:28.400
The vibe’s not great anymore.

00:32:37.560 --> 00:32:39.080
I’ll get going, May.

00:33:02.880 --> 00:33:03.920
Let’s go.

00:33:04.360 --> 00:33:05.400
You…

00:33:06.000 --> 00:33:07.240
What is this?

00:33:07.280 --> 00:33:09.400
You made me dress up for this place?

00:33:09.440 --> 00:33:12.400
I thought we were having some fancy dinner.

00:33:14.400 --> 00:33:15.800
So…

00:33:16.080 --> 00:33:18.760
What’s going on between you and May?

00:33:18.760 --> 00:33:20.240
I’m so confused.

00:33:20.280 --> 00:33:23.520
I thought you said you don’t meddle
in other people’s business.

00:33:24.960 --> 00:33:26.720
Then you don’t need to know.

00:33:27.240 --> 00:33:29.400
As for what I asked you to do today…

00:33:29.480 --> 00:33:31.200
you did great. That’s enough.

00:33:33.360 --> 00:33:34.800
Wait, wait…

00:33:35.840 --> 00:33:37.080
You’re leaving already?

00:33:37.560 --> 00:33:38.680
Yeah.

00:33:38.760 --> 00:33:42.000
But I haven’t eaten yet. I’m starving.

00:33:42.560 --> 00:33:45.600
Then pick a place you like.
I’ll take you there.

00:33:46.160 --> 00:33:49.200
Are you sure you want me to choose?

00:34:10.480 --> 00:34:12.520
This is my favorite place.

00:34:15.480 --> 00:34:17.600
You said you’d let me pick.

00:34:18.160 --> 00:34:19.320
You…

00:34:19.560 --> 00:34:21.240
You brought me here?

00:34:21.280 --> 00:34:23.080
Everyone’s going to recognize me.

00:34:25.080 --> 00:34:26.880
No. I’m not doing this.

00:34:27.360 --> 00:34:29.600
Hey, wait. Sit down first.

00:34:29.680 --> 00:34:31.760
You’ve got sunglasses and a hat in your car, right?

00:34:31.800 --> 00:34:33.280
Go get them.

00:34:33.280 --> 00:34:35.320
Wear sunglasses and a hat now?

00:34:35.680 --> 00:34:37.400
Wouldn’t that make me stand out more?

00:34:39.080 --> 00:34:41.360
You said I could choose the place.

00:34:41.360 --> 00:34:43.640
And I just helped you with May.

00:34:43.680 --> 00:34:45.840
And I’m really hungry right now.

00:34:45.880 --> 00:34:47.360
If I don’t eat,

00:34:47.400 --> 00:34:49.040
I might get sick.

00:34:49.040 --> 00:34:50.560
End up bedridden.

00:34:50.600 --> 00:34:53.120
And I have a screen test tomorrow.

00:34:53.280 --> 00:34:55.120
Fine, but…

00:34:55.160 --> 00:34:56.440
Eat fast and we leave.

00:34:56.480 --> 00:34:57.480
Okay?

00:34:57.640 --> 00:34:58.720
Okay?

00:35:01.080 --> 00:35:03.200
Miss, can we get a menu?

00:35:07.480 --> 00:35:08.600
What would you like?

00:35:09.680 --> 00:35:12.320
One papaya salad with
fermented fish and crab, please.

00:35:12.320 --> 00:35:15.760
Extra chili.
Make it super spicy and rich, please.

00:35:15.760 --> 00:35:17.280
One grilled pork.

00:35:17.320 --> 00:35:19.720
One grilled chicken and one sticky rice.

00:35:19.760 --> 00:35:22.000
- Do you want anything?
- No.

00:35:22.480 --> 00:35:23.880
That’s all for now.

00:35:24.160 --> 00:35:25.200
The menu, sir.

00:35:27.760 --> 00:35:32.760
And one plate of Soi Ju as well, please.

00:35:32.760 --> 00:35:35.320
- Soi Ju?
- Soi Ju.

00:35:44.880 --> 00:35:47.000
Is this tuna?

00:35:48.480 --> 00:35:49.680
Soi Ju.

00:35:49.760 --> 00:35:50.920
Ever heard of it?

00:35:51.280 --> 00:35:52.520
Want to try it?

00:35:52.760 --> 00:35:53.760
Here.

00:35:55.560 --> 00:35:57.120
Give it a try.

00:35:57.160 --> 00:35:58.880
This place is someone’s favorite, you know.

00:35:58.920 --> 00:36:01.720
I love coming here with my friends.
It’s really good.

00:36:11.480 --> 00:36:12.520
Here.

00:36:12.880 --> 00:36:15.680
Eat a lot. I ordered extra for you.

00:36:18.880 --> 00:36:19.880
What’s wrong?

00:37:20.760 --> 00:37:22.800
Weren’t you full earlier?

00:37:29.480 --> 00:37:31.440
When you pick a restaurant,

00:37:31.480 --> 00:37:34.200
at least ask if I can actually eat the food.

00:37:34.760 --> 00:37:37.880
It’s all good stuff.
How can you not eat it?

00:37:43.480 --> 00:37:45.120
You eat like a monster.

00:37:49.880 --> 00:37:52.200
So you’re really going back to acting?

00:37:54.880 --> 00:37:56.200
I already turned it down.

00:37:56.680 --> 00:37:58.400
Why, Win?

00:37:58.480 --> 00:38:01.640
If it were me, I’d never refuse.

00:38:01.680 --> 00:38:03.960
You’re living the life I dream of.

00:38:03.960 --> 00:38:07.440
Out of nowhere,
someone offers you a great script.

00:38:07.480 --> 00:38:11.000
You don’t have to run from casting to casting,
getting rejected every day like me.

00:38:17.600 --> 00:38:18.800
Do you know,

00:38:18.960 --> 00:38:21.600
this industry isn’t as beautiful as you think.

00:38:34.080 --> 00:38:35.880
Where’s the love?

00:38:36.280 --> 00:38:39.640
I’ve grown up all this time
and never once felt it.

00:38:39.680 --> 00:38:42.880
I’ve never even heard the word “love.”

00:38:44.680 --> 00:38:46.960
Even if it’s a lie, I still want to hear it.

00:38:46.960 --> 00:38:48.720
You wouldn’t understand

00:38:48.880 --> 00:38:51.480
what it’s like growing up alone,

00:38:51.480 --> 00:38:55.120
with no one who loves you.

00:38:56.160 --> 00:38:58.440
But you can’t tell me what love feels like either.

00:38:58.480 --> 00:39:00.000
You…

00:39:00.040 --> 00:39:01.040
Enough.

00:39:01.080 --> 00:39:03.440
Do you even really want to be an actress?

00:39:03.480 --> 00:39:05.840
I’m being serious right now.

00:39:05.840 --> 00:39:08.520
And this is how you’d perform for an audience?

00:39:08.560 --> 00:39:10.480
Yeah. So what?

00:39:10.960 --> 00:39:12.680
No wonder you never pass auditions.

00:39:12.760 --> 00:39:14.400
Look at the way you act.

00:39:14.440 --> 00:39:16.840
Why? What’s wrong with how I did it?

00:39:16.880 --> 00:39:18.560
What part wasn’t good?

00:39:18.560 --> 00:39:21.600
Go on, explain it, Ms. Superstar.

00:39:25.680 --> 00:39:27.640
What are you doing?

00:39:27.680 --> 00:39:29.280
Blocking.

00:39:30.360 --> 00:39:32.320
Every part of it was bad.

00:39:32.680 --> 00:39:36.560
Oh yeah? And you’re so good?
Why do you get to judge me?

00:39:36.560 --> 00:39:39.400
I was seriously trying, okay?

00:39:42.880 --> 00:39:44.120
Fine. I’ll show you.

00:39:48.840 --> 00:39:50.560
Where’s the love?

00:39:50.760 --> 00:39:52.640
Since the day I was born,

00:39:52.680 --> 00:39:55.480
I’ve never once felt it.

00:39:55.560 --> 00:39:59.800
I’ve never even heard the word “love.”

00:40:00.680 --> 00:40:02.800
Love isn’t just words.

00:40:03.560 --> 00:40:06.440
Anyone can lie with words.

00:40:08.880 --> 00:40:10.400
Even if it’s a lie,

00:40:10.680 --> 00:40:12.520
I still want to hear it.

00:40:13.280 --> 00:40:15.000
You don’t understand

00:40:15.080 --> 00:40:17.560
what it’s like growing up alone,

00:40:17.560 --> 00:40:19.000
with no one to love you.

00:40:19.160 --> 00:40:20.600
You wouldn’t get it.

00:40:36.360 --> 00:40:38.640
You’re not alone, though.

00:40:43.720 --> 00:40:44.760
But…

00:40:45.360 --> 00:40:47.920
you still can’t tell me

00:40:48.560 --> 00:40:50.920
what love really feels like.

00:40:52.160 --> 00:40:55.320
Have you ever loved someone that much?

00:40:57.960 --> 00:40:59.200
Yes.

00:41:01.280 --> 00:41:02.720
What was it like?

00:41:03.280 --> 00:41:05.520
Tell me.

00:41:08.160 --> 00:41:09.840
It’s a feeling inside.

00:41:09.880 --> 00:41:11.600
You can’t really put it into words.

00:41:15.360 --> 00:41:16.680
Then…

00:41:17.280 --> 00:41:19.600
how do you make them know

00:41:19.960 --> 00:41:22.720
that you love them?

00:41:26.280 --> 00:41:27.400
Well…

00:41:35.360 --> 00:41:36.800
Like this.

00:42:17.960 --> 00:42:19.920
That’s good acting.

00:42:21.160 --> 00:42:22.840
Good acting

00:42:23.160 --> 00:42:26.920
isn’t just memorizing lines
or copying someone else.

00:42:26.960 --> 00:42:29.200
It has to come from inside.

00:42:32.560 --> 00:42:34.000
So?

00:42:34.360 --> 00:42:36.120
Feel any different?

00:42:41.080 --> 00:42:43.000
Then that’s good.

00:42:43.760 --> 00:42:45.200
I’m going to shower.

00:43:55.760 --> 00:43:57.120
Wanneung.

00:43:59.680 --> 00:44:00.880
Win?

00:44:01.200 --> 00:44:03.080
I thought you went to see your friend.

00:44:03.440 --> 00:44:06.600
I just stopped to get gas. I’m heading out now.

00:44:07.280 --> 00:44:10.280
You’re going to your screen test, right?
Want me to drive you?

00:44:13.760 --> 00:44:15.840
You’re not planning anything again, are you?

00:44:16.800 --> 00:44:18.120
No.

00:44:19.080 --> 00:44:21.680
Or are you going to charge me for gas?

00:44:22.080 --> 00:44:23.800
I wouldn’t charge you.

00:44:32.880 --> 00:44:35.320
You can go.

00:44:50.080 --> 00:44:51.120
Can you...

00:44:51.120 --> 00:44:52.520
wish me luck?

00:44:52.520 --> 00:44:53.600
Do your best.

00:44:53.600 --> 00:44:55.920
You didn’t book anyone else today?

00:44:55.920 --> 00:44:58.840
I wanted Wanneung to have proper time
for a screen test.

00:44:58.840 --> 00:45:00.080
So I can pitch it.

00:45:14.442 --> 00:45:15.882
Turn right here.

00:45:16.242 --> 00:45:17.602
You can park right here.

00:45:25.642 --> 00:45:28.082
Thanks for the ride, Win.

00:45:29.762 --> 00:45:30.922
Can you...

00:45:30.922 --> 00:45:32.682
wish me luck?

00:45:36.762 --> 00:45:38.282
Do your best.

00:45:38.362 --> 00:45:40.682
And I hope you succeed.

00:45:42.042 --> 00:45:44.602
Amen.

00:45:47.442 --> 00:45:48.482
Hey…

00:45:48.562 --> 00:45:50.922
Can I borrow your phone to call mine?

00:45:50.962 --> 00:45:52.602
I can’t find it.

00:45:54.122 --> 00:45:55.402
Sure.

00:46:13.642 --> 00:46:15.202
Okay, I’m going now.

00:46:16.042 --> 00:46:17.282
Good luck.

00:46:17.642 --> 00:46:19.802
Okay.

00:46:41.962 --> 00:46:43.402
Hello.

00:46:53.322 --> 00:46:54.402
Wanneung...

00:46:54.442 --> 00:46:56.482
- Hi.
- Hello.

00:46:57.562 --> 00:46:58.642
You came alone?

00:46:58.682 --> 00:47:01.282
You told me to come alone, didn’t you?

00:47:02.042 --> 00:47:03.082
Good.

00:47:03.242 --> 00:47:04.282
So…

00:47:04.442 --> 00:47:07.122
You didn’t book anyone else today?

00:47:07.362 --> 00:47:08.522
I did.

00:47:08.842 --> 00:47:11.082
But I spaced them out.

00:47:11.322 --> 00:47:15.122
I wanted Wanneung to have proper time
for a screen test.

00:47:15.162 --> 00:47:16.722
So I can pitch it.

00:47:16.762 --> 00:47:18.402
People need to see your talent.

00:47:19.242 --> 00:47:20.282
Ready?

00:47:21.562 --> 00:47:23.002
Yes.

00:47:23.642 --> 00:47:24.642
Let’s go.

00:47:24.682 --> 00:47:26.082
This way.

00:47:27.242 --> 00:47:28.442
Over here.

00:48:01.762 --> 00:48:03.402
I’ve got a film script.

00:48:03.442 --> 00:48:05.522
The director’s looking for a lead actress.

00:48:05.762 --> 00:48:07.602
But the role is a bit sexy.

00:48:07.722 --> 00:48:09.762
You’d have to show some skin.

00:48:10.162 --> 00:48:11.562
If you’re brave enough,

